[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Patterns extraction with machine learning process annotated and unannotated text have been explored extensively by academic researchers.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] However, researchers recognized several challenges in developing fixed sets of rules for expressions respectably.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Much of the challenges in rule development stems from the nature of textual information.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Six challenges have been recognized by several researchers: 1) metaphorical expressions, 2) discrepancies in writings, 3) context-sensitive, 4) represented words with fewer usages, 5) time-sensitive, and 6) ever-growing volume.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] For the text obtained from the Internet, the discrepancies in the writing style of targeted text data involve distinct writing genres and styles.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Classification may vary based on the subjectiveness or objectiveness of previous and following sentences.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] The task is challenged by some textual data's time-sensitive attribute.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] If a group of researchers wants to confirm a piece of fact in the news, they need a longer time for cross-validation, than the news becomes outdated.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] The task is also challenged by the sheer volume of textual data.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] The textual data's ever-growing nature makes the task overwhelmingly difficult for the researchers to complete the task on time.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Previously, the research mainly focused on document level classification.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] However, classifying a document level suffers less accuracy, as an article may have diverse types of expressions involved.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Researching evidence suggests a set of news articles that are expected to dominate by the objective expression, whereas the results show that it consisted of over 40% of subjective expression.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] To overcome those challenges, researchers conclude that classifier efficacy depends on the precisions of patterns learner.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] And the learner feeds with large volumes of annotated training data outperformed those trained on less comprehensive subjective features.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] However, one of the main obstacles to executing this type of work is to generate a big dataset of annotated sentences manually.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Manual annotation task is a meticulous assignment, it require intense concentration to finish.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Manual annotation task is an assiduous work.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Riloff (1996) show that a 160 texts cost 8 hours for one annotator to finish.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] All these mentioned reasons can impact on the efficiency and effectiveness of subjective and objective classification.
[src:sentiment-analysis-nlp/sentiment-analysis] Accordingly, two bootstrapping methods were designed to learning linguistic patterns from unannotated text data.
